The paper discusses distributed data storage systems and their transactional functionality, which falls under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC), databases (cs.DB), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the limitations and compromises of highly available systems, which could fall under the category of security and cryptography (cs.CR) or systems and control (cs.SY).
